{
  "texts": [
    "Based on the morphing ratio, each face was ranked from 1 (100% sad face) to 50 (100% happy face).",
    "These rankings were closely associated with participants' own rankings of each face when observed one by one (b = 0.8; t(50) = 26.25; P < 0.001; see Supplementary Results).",
    "We created 100 unique arrays of 12 faces for each participant.",
    "The average ranking of the 12 faces in half of the arrays was smaller than 25.5 (thus, the array was more sad) and greater than 25.5 in the other half (thus the array was more happy).",
    "Bias in this task was defined as the difference between the average responses of a participant across all trials and the actual average."
  ]
}